# AI Assistant Rules

## Philosophy
- Minimalism.
- Simple is better.
- Clean code, easy to read.
- Functional Programming.

## Tech Stack
- Runtime: Node.js, Bun, Deno
- Database: PostgreSQL, Redis, Meilisearch
- Backend: HonoJS
- Templating: VentoJS
- Frontend: Svelte, Astro
- Styling: Native CSS (No Tailwind)
- Language: JavaScript with JSDocs (No TypeScript)

## Coding Standards
- Read `.ai/CODING_STANDARDS.md` for more info
- Respect eslint.config.js

## When Writing Code
- Read existing code patterns first
- Follow the current coding style
- Apply functional programming thinking
- Handle errors explicitly
- Keep dependencies minimal

## Security Rules (CRITICAL)
- NEVER output or request .env and example.env file contents
- NEVER hardcode API keys, passwords, or secrets
- NEVER send sensitive data to external AI services
- Follow .aiignore file for excluded files
- Read `.ai/SECURITY_POLICY.md` for more info

## Testing
- Write tests for critical business logic
- Use simple test runners (node:test, bun:test, vitest)
- No complex mocking frameworks unless necessary

## When in Doubt
- Ask for clarification before generating code.

## Guideline for AI Agents
- Read `.ai/README.md` to get overview.
